annotation.TEXT: Oh, there have been tweaks made here! Instead of a P-switch, there's a shell, two coin-giving clouds, and some turn block bridges.
..."Subtly different", eh?
A shell, eh? So, do I kick it straight up to hit an off screen block that the arrow is pointing to?
Umm... What? The switch palace didn't collapse. However, I still can't reenter it, even if I press L and R together.
Also, I guess waffledoctor87 removed the Banzai Bill that was here as well, probably so it wouldn't interfere with someone running up the yellow wall, I guess.
Yeah, I thought there was one more that I hadn't killed yet. Now, after getting past this pipe and bullet cannon, things get trickier.
Hey, this pipe's new, and I can go down it.
Whoops, so much for that shell. I hope I didn't really need it for anything.
Demo count: Psyche!
Looks like the same message to me. Doesn't appear anything's been changed here.

Okay, so it looks like we've got one of those backwards ? blocks that acts like a slope going down and to the right here. Let me see if I can scroll the screen up so that we can get a better look at it.
Any more tweaks to the level? Or is it all untouched from here on out?
There we go. (Also, I assume that other block just gave me a flower.)
Yep, now that I've ditched the key, that Banzai Bill was able to show up. Is this also true for the other Banzai Bill near the yellow dotted block wall?
7-life combo!
Of course, it would help if I didn't accidentally climb back up the mountain... LOL.
Well, right away I see a new level dot over here to the left of Yoshi's Island 1.
That message appears to be unchanged.
Still don't know what the shell's for, if anything, but I guess I'll take it with me.
With all of the fish around here, fireballs are very helpful. Of course, you can also wait for low tide and kick them while they're flopping.
Raise your hands if you thought I was actually dead for a second there!
Bah, all that effort trying to time that properly and I only got 30.
To be continued... Yo!
Done! BTW, waffledoctor87, if there's another exit in this level (like with a normal goal), let me know!
Huh, I guess this fish never spawned earlier. Well, whatever. It's no threat now.
That message is also unchanged.
Ah, and that takes me to the new level, which is called Disappearing Tides. However, I think I'm going to go to the Yellow Switch Palace first.

...well, it doesn't say it here, but the name of this hack is Super Tweak World! It's made by waffledoctor87, who requested that I beta test it. Alright, I don't think there have been any changes to the title screen or demo, so let's just get started here!
Gah! Stupid ascending glitch! That should've totally counted as me stomping the fish! The ascending glitch irritates me every time it happens.
Alternatively, I can wait for low tide, and then use the springboard to both hit the ? block, and then jump on top of it, like this.
Is this bonus room any different?
However, that's not the intended solution either. Now, I'm going to pretend I didn't activate the eating block yet, and just proceed through the level.
Am I just not jumping high enough, or... Oh!
Whoa, hello!
Well, for right now, I'm going to return to YI1 and get the other exit.
No, it looks the same to me. Oh, well... Push!
Umm... It looks the same to me. waffledoctor87, I'm surprised you didn't tweak this bonus room at all.
Also, assuming the sprite limit doesn't keep him from spawning, watch out for this Sumo Bro. He can't summon flames from his position here, but he's still an unstompable, non-flammable obstacle.
So, will this take me to that new level dot?
And, that was me being careless. I really should've just stayed low in the water to avoid those cheep-cheeps.
Alright, I think I'm done playing for today. Next time, I'll be starting with Yoshi's Island 2!
Yep, which means waffledoctor87 didn't actually remove any of the Banzai Bills.
Well, that's weird. Alright, now let's check out the new level, Disappearing Tides!
...Umm, no?
There's some ice blocks and a keyhole. So, I guess this level has a secret exit, which I would assume leads to that new level dot on the map.
I think this level needs more tweaking. In fact, I don't think there were any changes to the sprites aside from the keyhole, key, and eating block.
There's now a wall triangle here, for whatever reason.
Yeah, apparently, when a message box removes the layer 3 water, a little bit of the layer 3 water still actually exists below the screen, and I already knew this, so I figured I'd be okay there.
Oh, nice! That diagonal pipe now functions as a cannon!
There we go! I knew you could do it!
Killing as many fish as you can is a good idea so that you won't have to deal with them later, because we're gonna be going back and forth through this level a few times.

Well, while I'm here, I may as well double-check to make sure I can't reenter the Yellow Switch Palace, and I can't. Okay, now go back down and press LEFT this time to move Mario onto Disappearing Tides!
Ooh, found the key. Now I just need to locate a P-switch. Hmm... I wonder what this arrow is pointing at?
OKay, that's enough of that. Now, take this key, and... Uh, oh!
There's also a Thwimp that looks like a Bob-omb. I wonder if this shell is in the proper sprite slot...
Oh, I can grab a flower while I'm here, since the pipe cannon reset the level earlier.
Looks like I'll need the springboard to get over this pipe again.
Oh, looks like the sprite limit caused a Thwimp-omb to not spawn earlier. I'd like to knock it over with this shell if I can.
Now, there's no real hint that you need to do this, but hit the P-switch here to make ? blocks appear to the right.
I probably don't need the key this time, but I guess I'll take it with me.
So, I guess the arrow was pointing to that hidden 1-up. But then, why give me the shell?
Looks like the last few screens of this level weren't altered at all.
Hello, this is SomeGuy712x, and welcome to...
Alright, let's give Yoshi's Island 1 a go, then.
Ah, this message is different!
Also, since Yoshi's Island 1 now has two exits, it should have a red level dot instead of a yellow one now. You should probably change that, waffledoctor87.
...Um, what?
Whoops. Gimme my key back. Why can't Mario keep a grip on something as he's being shot from a cannon anyway?
Ooh, there's some new stuff here-- A ? block and a coin arrow.
Definitely try to fry the hammer guy if you can!

And, with the water removed due to the message box, this is when you're apparently supposed to bounce off of the springboard to hit the ? block above, so you can activate the eating block, which frees this P-switch. Now, carry the P-switch back to the right...
Goal tape average so far: 30 / 1 = 30 stars each.
Fortunately, it doesn't look like I'm having that issue.
Huh. I thought I'd be able to hit that ? block just by bouncing from the note block just right, but whatever. I can just wait until high tide.
Boink! And now I can activate the eating block. However, this is actually not waffledoctor87's intended solution.
Well, I just went up the path to the Yellow Switch Palace, but without actually revealing the path. waffledoctor87, I think that might need some tweaking.
Stomping combo, yo!
Now, in waffledoctor87's video that I linked to earlier, the flying cheepos here must've been hitting the sprite limit and were interfering with this bullet cannon's ability to fire.
It looks like there's no other differences in the overworld map, though. I guess I'll start by taking a look at Yoshi's house.
Awesome combo! (8 hits) 1-life combo!
Ooh, there's something different over here. Looks like I'll want to come back after hitting the Yellow Switch Palace.

Nice! That Thwimp-omb is defeated! Now, I did miss a coin there, but that's okay, because... Yeah! If there's multiple coin-clouds present at once, grabbing ten of their coins in total will cause them to start spitting out 1-ups for the rest of their durations!
Go, my yellow blocks, and fill the world with your yellowness!

No Banzai Bill here either? ...Oh, wait. I think I know what happened. When I carried this key through the pipe, it was placed in sprite slot 0, and that sprite slot is the only slot that Banzai Bills can appear in, so as long as this key is around, no Banzai Bills will appear.
Looking back, I probably could've used the note block to reach the keyhole, but whatever.

Huh, looks like there's a sprite memory issue which causes this shell to become invisible while a Banzai Bill is present. (But, looking back, the shell only vanished in the presence of the Banzai Bill here while I was turning around. That's weird.)
So, the objective here is to hit this ? block to turn it into a brown used block, and then stand on it to activate the eating block to the left.
Whoa! Okay, that's clever! Well, it looks like I'll be getting the secret exit first here!
Yeah, so I don't know why waffledoctor87 put that backwards ? block there, but whatever.
I wonder if anything's changed in the second room...
Uh, oh. Hitting this message box removed the layer 3 water! Also, there's now a cheepo generator here as well! At this point, you've gotta return to the start of the level.
Be careful not to bump into the munchers on the turn blocks. They'll bite, even if you hit their stems from below.
Agh! It looked for a second like I was just barely gonna stay ahead of the shell there, but that stupid turn block bridge messed up my momentum!
Alright, and with this key, I can finally finish this level!
Oh, hey! I recognize this level! waffledoctor87 already made a video of it. Click here to see it. (SOUND CH 6 DISABLED)
